4. NEVER fall back to USP <467> master regulatory limit
5. If no vendor evidence exists for that solvent in the annexure: render "NA"
(component has annexure but no specific evidence)

For final USP <467> comparison row:
- ALWAYS use USP <467> master regulatory limit
- Do not use vendor content values
- Do not use vendor spec values

Detection rules for content extraction from annexure:
- Text patterns for actual content: "X ppm", "X.Y ppm", "measured X ppm",
"actual X ppm", "content X ppm", "found X ppm"
- Text patterns for spec limit: "NMT X ppm", "Not more than X ppm", "≤ X ppm"
- Text patterns for compendial reference: "as per USP/NF X ppm", "EP X ppm",
"USP <467> X ppm"

When both actual and spec exist for same solvent in same annexure:
- Prefer actual content value (Column A priority)
- If actual is BDL/BQL/ND: use spec limit as worst-case (previously locked fix)

Absolute rule:
Ingredient row content cells and Comparison row cells must come from 
different data sources. Never confuse them. Never fall back from vendor 
